From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mark Harfouche <mark.harfouche@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 6 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] vsx: add v_fma overload for v_int32x4

The VSX HAL defines `v_muladd(v_int32x4, v_int32x4, v_int32x4)` as a
manual `v_add(v_mul(a, b), c)` fallback, but it never defines the
matching `v_fma` overload — `OPENCV_HAL_IMPL_VSX_MULADD` is only
instantiated for `v_float32x4` / `v_float64x2`. Every other backend
(NEON, SSE, AVX2, MSA, LSX, RVV, WASM, …) ships an integer `v_fma`.

OpenCV 5.0's new imgproc warp kernels rely on the integer overload:

    #define CV_WARP_VECTOR_GET_ADDR_C1() \
        v_int32 addr_0 = v_fma(v_srcstep, src_iy0, src_ix0), \
                addr_1 = v_fma(v_srcstep, src_iy1, src_ix1);

so on ppc64le the build of modules/imgproc/src/imgwarp.cpp fails with
"no matching function for call to v_fma(v_int32, v_int32, v_int32)".

Add the missing overload mirroring the existing v_muladd one.
---
 modules/core/include/opencv2/core/hal/intrin_vsx.hpp | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/modules/core/include/opencv2/core/hal/intrin_vsx.hpp b/modules/core/include/opencv2/core/hal/intrin_vsx.hpp
index 0a0915a..b3acd68 100644
--- a/modules/core/include/opencv2/core/hal/intrin_vsx.hpp
+++ b/modules/core/include/opencv2/core/hal/intrin_vsx.hpp
@@ -1057,6 +1057,9 @@ inline _Tpvec v_muladd(const _Tpvec& a, const _Tpvec& b, const _Tpvec& c)   \
 OPENCV_HAL_IMPL_VSX_MULADD(v_float32x4)
 OPENCV_HAL_IMPL_VSX_MULADD(v_float64x2)
 
+inline v_int32x4 v_fma(const v_int32x4& a, const v_int32x4& b, const v_int32x4& c)
+{ return v_add(v_mul(a,  b), c); }
+
 inline v_int32x4 v_muladd(const v_int32x4& a, const v_int32x4& b, const v_int32x4& c)
 { return v_add(v_mul(a,  b), c); }
 
